cs.DB, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.CE, cs.CR 

This paper focuses on evaluating and comparing two processing engines, MapReduce and Spark, for Big Data processing using the BigBench benchmark. The paper discusses the setup of an experimental Hadoop cluster and the execution of BigBench on both Hive and Spark SQL. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DB (databases), cs.DC (distributed, parallel, and cluster computing), and cs.DS (data structures and algorithms). Additionally, the paper also discusses resource utilization and performance evaluation, which could fall under cs.CE (computational engineering, finance, and science) and cs.CR (cryptography and security).
